headlines.description: — Dalano Banton scored a career-high 27 points and Chris Boucher added 20 as the short-handed Toronto Raptors snapped a three-game losing streak with a 115-111 win over the Detroit Pistons on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blanton, Boucher lead short-handed Raptors past Pistons

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 17 points and nine assists, and the Charlotte Hornets stopped an eight-game slide with a 112-105 victory over the Orlando Magic on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets stop 8-game slide with 112-105 win against Magic

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Marcus Smart scored 20 of his 22 points in the second half, and the Boston Celtics beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 126-122 on Monday night for their seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smart helps Celtics beat Thunder for 7th straight win
Adebayo scores 30, Heat storm back to stun Suns 113-112

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 22 points in three quarters to lead the Los Angeles Clippers to 122-106 rout of the Houston Rockets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 22 to lead Clippers to 122-106 rout of Rockets

headlines.description: — De’Andre Hunter scored 24 points and Trae Young had 21 points and nine assists, leading the Atlanta Hawks to a 121-106 victory over Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hunter, Young lead Hawks past Giannis, Bucks 121-106

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole's bobblehead doll was a big hit — and the real guy himself sure shined, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 36 on bobblehead night, Warriors rout Spurs
